epresent the country in athletics, rowing and swimming.\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the athletics field, Zimbabwe will be represented by sprinters Makanakaishe Charamba and Tapiwanashe Makarawu, who both qualified for the 200m dash, while Isaac Mpofu and Rutendo Nyahora will partake in the marathon.\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 447, \"end\": 455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zimbabwe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.791167528216211e-18, \"text\": \"Zimbabwe\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zimbabwe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zimbabwe\"}, {\"begin\": 597, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rutendo_Nyahora\", \"score\": 0.9999999990875494, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rutendo Nyahora\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rutendo_Nyahora\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rutendo_Nyahora\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paige van der Westhuizen and Denilson Cyprianos will represent the country in swimming while Stephen Cox will compete in rowing.\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_van_der_Westhuizen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paige van der Westhuizen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_van_der_Westhuizen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_van_der_Westhuizen\"}, {\"begin\": 673, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Den\\u00edlson_(footballer,_born_1976)\", \"score\": 0.5454545450629641, \"rank\": 0.8333333333332769, \"text\": \"Denilson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Den\\u00edlson_(footballer,_born_1976)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Den\\u00edlson_(footballer,_born_1976)\"}, {\"begin\": 73